    "summary": "I am a result-oriented professional with a Big 4 background, who is used to work with small professional teams. For sundry years I am engaged in sundry roles on the cutting edge of business, finance, processes and IT (i.e. SAP). Recently I have - as business consultant at ING - realised the development and roll-out of shared systems and processes to i.e. London and Frankfurt. Part of this work is also drafting project plans, working with scrum-teams and making trade-offs between tactical and strategic solutions. I have got international experiences in USA, UK, Canada (Nova Scotia), Kingdom of Saudi-Arabia and in Europe. In my work I am looking for a balance between convincing, chasing on deadlines and thinking with the (internal) client. Verbally and in writing I am communicating clear and accessible taking into account other stakeholders.\n\nSpecialties: \n\u2022 Holding controller\n\u2022 Real estate business\n\u2022 Implementation decisions Board of Management\n\u2022 Implementation internal control framework\n\u2022 Management Accounting\n\u2022 Support Management during business critical IT projects\n\u2022 Improvement of financial process, accounting system, treasury control, consolidation process and reporting\n\u2022 Outsourcing, shared service centers and ISAE3402 / SAS70 statements\n\u2022 Monitoring Compliance in processes\n\u2022 Financial Audit and Operational Audits\n\u2022 Advisory re internal audit dept and audit committees\n\u2022 Lid Raad van Toezicht (aandachtsgebied financi\u00ebn)\n\u2022 Security affairs, front running and fraud.",
